<br>
<br>
I personally think this would be a huge mistake. Sure it sounds good on paper, since it would be good for the “economy,” but in practice, it sucks ass. I’m thinking back to my UO days here, but I remember having to carry around spare sets of armor and weapons wherever I went in case something broke. Hoarding 20 or more suits of armor and sets of weapons in my house figuring I’d need them some day. Rarely using my best weapons and armor for fear they would break. Having to leave dungeon crawls to run to town to get my weapons/armor fixed. I’m sorry, but it is just plain annoying. Almost as annoying as spell reagents *cringe*.<br>
<br>
Plus, if equipment brakes, you can never get attached to or identify yourself with a piece of equipment. Many people have a personal goal to attain a piece of equipment, and that keeps them playing. To me, equipment decay completely ruins that aspect of the game. Not to mention that you’ll have to equip and dequip stuff all the time to repair or replace it as it get broken/worn. Whereas now in EQ, you just equiup your best stuff and go with it.<br>
<br>
<br>
