<br>
One of my all-time favourite single-player games was the CRPG &quot;Betrayal at Krondor&quot;.  That game uses armour and weapon decay very well.  If you've got a good smith, you can fix it up good as new.  If you don't want to bother, you can also just keep a spare set handy.  Too bad the sequels didn't live up to the original.  =p<br>
<br>
This has implications on camping, by the way.  If items are going to be breaking and *leaving* the game more frequently, then they must also *enter* the game more frequently, thus drop rates can (and must) increase.<br>
<br>
I like the focus that they're putting on tradeskills.  Right now, tradeskills are really only useful for quests - by the time you're tough enough to kill the mobs whose rare drop is required for a particular recipe, the item produced is useless (mechanically).  I just hope they balance things out so everybody doesn't end up as a smith...<br>
